{
  "text": "Overall, Spearman rank-order correlation tests show high interrater agreement. The test statistics range from q = 0.237 to 0.847 with associated p-values ranging from 0.12 to 0.00 (with one exception where q = 0.054; p < 0.10). Significance levels under the 90% confidence level thereby occur only when raters have less than 60 pictures in common. Even so, [CITATION_1] show that their findings are robust to whether individuals evaluate over 500 pictures or only 4, which suggests that the properties of the rating distribution are not overly sensitive to the number of evaluations. Following the 'truth of consensus' method [CITATION_2] , we calculate the average of the independent evaluations across raters for a given politician on each of the five characteristics.",
